      "id": "PopularPost287677",
      "post_content": "@General\\_Naga: Why shouldn't white have card draw? Every color has card draw, even red; while red has less than green and black, it has more than white and will get more in the future. Every color should have access to card draw, as it is essential to playing Magic, and this card feels much more white than blue, as white is the color of community. Blue should still get cards like [Trade Secrets](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Trade Secrets) and [Flux](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Flux) which require a lot of thinking from opponents, and should be able to keep the really huge everyone-draws cards like [Jace's Archivist](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Jace's Archivist), but the little stuff like this feels very much more white, and would be rated higher in white as well as that color has less draw competing for slots in decks.",
      "posted_by": "sarroth",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost287677\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_post\">@General_Naga: Why shouldn't white have card draw? Every color has card draw, even red; while red has less than green and black, it has more than white and will get more in the future. Every color should have access to card draw, as it is essential to playing Magic, and this card feels much more white than blue, as white is the color of community. Blue should still get cards like <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Trade Secrets\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Trade Secrets\">Trade Secrets</a> and <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Flux\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Flux\">Flux</a> which require a lot of thinking from opponents, and should be able to keep the really huge everyone-draws cards like <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Jace's Archivist\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Jace's Archivist\">Jace's Archivist</a>, but the little stuff like this feels very much more white, and would be rated higher in white as well as that color has less draw competing for slots in decks.</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '287677'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy20957\">sarroth</span>\r\n         